what is the fastest road legal car?

The fastest street-legal car right now is the Koenigsegg Jesko Absolut. It can go up to 300 mph and has a 5.6-liter twin-turbo V8 engine with 1,949 horsepower. Used to be the Koenigsegg Agera RS and Bugatti Chiron holding the records. 🏎️💨
does it beat the bugatti chiron super sport too1?

Yo, it's a close call between the Koenigsegg Jesko Absolut and Bugatti Chiron Super Sport! 🏁

- Jesko's got sick acceleration with 1625 PS. 🚀
- Chiron's top speed is 304.77 mph, but they cap customer cars at 261 mph for safety. 🚎💨

So, if you're into quick starts, Jesko's your ride. But for top speed, Chiron's the beast! 🏆

[Source](https://zeperfs.com/en/duel8395-9699.htm)
how much do each of them cost?

The Koenigsegg Jesko Absolut costs around €3,000,000, while the Bugatti Chiron Super Sport 300+ is between €3,000,000 and €3,500,000. For more details, check this [link](https://zeperfs.com/en/match7849-9699.htm).
